Minimum Expected Contents
  1) Appointment Decision
     - Formal appointment of the named individual as Data Protection Officer (DPO)
     - Effective date of appointment and duration/conditions (if applicable)
     - Reference to governance basis (Board resolution, decision ID/date)
  2) Identity and Contact Details of the DPO
     - Full legal name and professional title
     - Primary email, telephone, postal address
     - Publication statement (contact details will be published and provided to the Supervisory Authority)
  3) Position in the Organization and Reporting Line
     - Reporting directly to the highest management level (e.g., CEO/Board)
     - Statement of DPO independence and freedom from conflicts of interest
     - Assurances on protection from dismissal or penalties for performing duties (GDPR Art. 38)
  4) Scope of Responsibilities (GDPR Articles 37–39)
     - Informing/advising the controller/processor and employees on GDPR and data protection obligations
     - Monitoring compliance and assignment of responsibilities, awareness-raising, training, audits
     - Advising on DPIAs and monitoring their performance (GDPR Art. 35)
     - Cooperation and point of contact with the Supervisory Authority (Hellenic DPA)
     - Keeping records of processing activities (where applicable) and advising on retention
     - Ensuring privacy by design and by default in QTS processes and systems
  5) Resources and Access
     - Confirmation that adequate resources, budget, tools, and support are provided
     - Access to necessary personal data and processing operations
     - Access to other business units (e.g., PKI/RA operations, Security, Legal, HR) to perform tasks
  6) Independence and Conflict of Interest
     - Statement that the DPO will not receive instructions regarding task performance
     - Clarification that the DPO holds no role that determines purposes/means of processing
     - Conflict of interest assessment outcome and mitigation measures
  7) Replacement/Deputy Arrangements
     - Designated deputy DPO or process for ensuring continuity (if applicable)
     - Handover and coverage procedures (leave/absence)
  8) Training, Qualifications, and Confidentiality
     - Statement of expert knowledge of data protection law and practices
     - Ongoing training/CPD commitments
     - Confidentiality obligations pursuant to GDPR and national law
  9) Notifications and Publications
     - Commitment to notify/publish DPO contact details on the website and to the Hellenic DPA
     - Internal communication to employees and applicable processors/sub-processors
  10) Acknowledgements and Signatures
      - Authorized signatory(ies) of GreekTrustCo (name, title, date)
      - DPO acknowledgement signature (name, date)

